# CryptoHub

## Overview

CryptoHub serves as your central hub for all things crypto. This repository aims to provide a comprehensive resource for cryptocurrency enthusiasts, developers, and researchers, offering real-time data, educational resources, community discussions, and more.

## Features

- **Real-Time Market Data**: Access up-to-date prices, market capitalizations, and trading volumes for cryptocurrencies.
- **Educational Resources**: Tutorials, articles, and guides on blockchain technology, cryptocurrencies, and decentralized finance (DeFi).
- **Community Discussions**: Forums and discussions on various cryptocurrency topics, fostering collaboration and knowledge sharing.
- **Developer Tools**: Resources and tools for blockchain developers, including APIs, SDKs, and smart contract templates.
- **News and Updates**: Stay informed with the latest news, announcements, and trends in the crypto space.

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

Ensure you have the following installed:
- [Node.js](https://nodejs.org/) (version 14 or later)
- [npm](https://www.npmjs.com/) (version 6 or later)

### Installation

1. Clone the repository:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/your-username/CryptoHub.git
   cd CryptoHub
